description: This large southern room in the Workers Dormitory is used to feed
the workers who dwell here.  Taking up most of the south side of the
building it expands outwards with a room filled with tables.  At the
far southeast corner is a L shaped table from which the food is
served.  Large windows looks southward towards Castle Vector.  There
is nothing more special about this room, it looks the same as every
other room.
6933.name: {B[{CW{corkers {CD{cormitory{B] {CMess Hall{x

description: The unwed men of Vector City are given living quarters here at the
Workers Dormitory as part of their work program.  Before you is the
'Boys' Corridor, a large room filled with bunk beds.  Everyone is
given a little space to dwell in, each of the bunk beds are spread
apart enough to allow the top occupant to use the left side of the
bunk bed as his, and the bottom occupant to use the right.  Large
windows on the northern and western wall look out at the small grass
area between the building and industrial zone wall.

description: A medium size lobby opens up revealing the Workers Dormitory of the
Vectorian Industrial Sector.  This building is where workers with no
homes are suppose to live while serving their country, and earning a
well wage.  Those with families are given homes in the newly developed
Vector City.  There is nothing special about this lobby, a few benches
to sit on.  South is the door to the main office, a window built into
the door reveals a secretary post behind it.  There is a door in the
north wall which reads [Boy's Living Cooridor].  A large hallway
stretches east.

description: This hallway stretches east to west in the Workers Dormitory.
There is nothing special about it.  The walls are white plaster and
the floor is white tile.  Westwards a single door to the south can be
seen, and the exit into the buildings lobby.  Eastwards there are
three doors, two on the south wall and one on the northwall.  At the
end of the hall is a large glass window which stretches from ceiling
to floor.

description: You stand in the Eastern part of the lobby.  Here there is a bench
for sitting, and a large clock.  You can hear something that sounds
like a train coming from the east.  The lobby spreads out in most of
the other directions.

description: You stand in the Western Part of the lobby.  Here before you stands
a large painting of Ganon Vector, the bloodline ruler.  A doorway here
leads off into the western wings of Vector.  Back east is the center
of the lobby, and the other corners of it too.

description: The unmarried women who live in Vector City are given living space
here at the Workers Dormitory in the Living Corridors.  This area of
the dormitory is a large open room filled with bunk beds, each spaced
out to give its occupant enough room to live in.  The top bunk gets
the left side, and the bottom bunk gets the right.  Its said that life
is well maintained in here by those who live here helping each other
out, keeping everything clean and organized.  There are no guards and
so peace must be maintained by themselves.  Windows on the northern
and eastern walls reveal the small grass area between the building and
the brick wall around the Industrial Zone.

description: The hallway stretches east to west inside the Workers Dormitory.
Eastwards further down the hall a few others doors can be seen.  There
is a door here southwards which reads 'Mess Hall'.  There is nothing
else here, no pictures on the wall or furniture, just white walls and
white floors.
6925.name: {B[{CW{corkers {CD{cormitory{B] {CEast Hallway{x

description: This room is very clean and probably very sterile.  There are
several counters and cabinets which line the walls and a large bed in
the center.  The counters are filled with metal and wooden tools,
potions and hermbs.  A large Magicite Lamp hangs over th If a worker
here at the dormitory gets injured they come here to be healed.  When
such a problem does occur a nurse and doctor are called in from the
city, who use this room as their office and lab.  There is a window on
the eastern and southern wall, and only one door.

description: The East Hallway of the Dormitory ends here, a large window which
expands from floor to ceiling stands on the eastern wall.  Outside the
brick wall of the industrial zone can be seen, and beyond that is the
City Orphanage.  A doorway in the northern wall reads 'Girls Living
Cooridor'.  Southwards another wooden door reads 'Medical Office'.
Westwards the hallway extends most of the length of the Workers
Dormitory.  On the southern wall there are two wood doors, one only a
few feet from here and the other at the far end.
6928.name: {B[{CW{corkers {CD{cormitory{B] {CEast Hallway{x

description: A large desk stands offset to the northern door leading into the
workers dormitory's lobby.  This desk is used by the secretary which
occupies this room, and keeps track of the workers who come and go out
the front door.  It is also used for security measures and at night a
guard replaces the secretary, and no one is allowed in or out after a
certain time.  The office is somewhat small and square, the walls are
covered in tacked papers and maps.  There are some small shelves built
into the wall holding records and books for the Workers Dormitory.
